5|$|Lowell is {{considered}} one of the Fireside Poets, a group of writers from New England in the 1840s who all had a substantial national following and whose work was often read aloud <b>by</b> <b>the</b> family <b>fireplace.</b> Besides Lowell, <b>the</b> main figures from this group were Longfellow, Holmes, John Greenleaf Whittier, and William Cullen Bryant.|$|R
