50|$|Five civilians {{managed to}} survive: two adults and three children. They {{pretended to be}} dead among the corpses and then escaped from <b>the</b> burning {{buildings}} <b>by</b> ascending from <b>the</b> <b>fireplace.</b> Most of <b>the</b> local adults {{were not in the}} village {{at the time of the}} attack because they were working in adjacent villages, and thus they escaped death.|$|R
